Ranked By

1.8K votes

Voting Rules

Vote up the best tennis players from the Czech Republic.

List of the best tennis players from Czech Republic, listed by popularity with photos of the players when available. Czech Republic has produced some very talented tennis players over the years, including both men and women. These are some of the most talented Czech tennis players to ever live, so if you're a native of Czech Republic and are aspiring to play tennis professionally then these people should be your idols. If you're searching for a particular popular tennis player from Czech Republic then you can use the "search" box to find who you're looking for.

List includes Jan Kodeš, Lukáš Dlouhý and more.

This list answers the questions, "Who are the greatest Czech tennis players?" and "Who is the best Czech tennis player of all time?"

You can click on the names of these legendary tennis players of Czech Republic in order to get more information about each one. If you play tennis or just love the sport then use this list of talented Czech tennis players to find some athletes you haven't heard of before.

Most divisive: Květa Peschke

Over 500 Ranker voters have come together to rank this list of Czech Players

1

132 VOTES

Arguably one of the greatest tennis players of all time, Martina Navratilova's impact on the sport transcends national boundaries and establishes her as a true global icon. Boasting an incredible all-court game and unparalleled athleticism, Navratilova redefined the women's game during her illustrious career and inspired countless future stars to follow her path. Her unwavering passion and dedication to the sport continue to shape its future, solidifying her status as a Czech tennis legend.

Birthplace : Czech Republic, Prague

Nationality : United States of America, Czechoslovakia

2

151 VOTES

An aggressive baseline player with a powerful left-handed serve, Petra Kvitová consistently proves herself as one of the top Czech tennis talents in recent years. Known for her strong groundstrokes and fast court coverage, Kvitová often overpowers opponents with her ability to dictate points from the back of the court. Her enduring presence at the highest level of the women's game not only demonstrates her unparalleled skill but also highlights the depth and thriving nature of Czech tennis talent.

3

75 VOTES

Jana Novotná

A versatile and highly skilled player, Jana Novotná was known for her exceptional volleying prowess and aggressive serve-and-volley style of play. Among the pantheon of Czech tennis greats, Novotná stood out not only for her singles success but also for her remarkable achievements in doubles and mixed doubles. A true ambassador for the sport, her tenacity and relentless pursuit of victory underscored the fighting spirit that Czech tennis is known for.

Birthplace : Brno, Jihovýchod, Czech Republic

Nationality : Czech Republic

4

107 VOTES

Renowned for his strong serve and powerful groundstrokes, Tomáš Berdych has long been a mainstay in the upper echelons of men's tennis. His consistent performances against the world's best combined with his stoic demeanor and unwavering commitment to his craft make him a prime example of Czech tennis excellence. Berdych's versatile game and adaptability across all surfaces highlight the depth and breadth of talent hailing from the Czech Republic.

Birthplace : Valašské Meziříčí, Czech Republic

Nationality : Czech Republic

5

37 VOTES

Widely regarded as one of the finest clay-court players of his era, Jan Kodeš carved out a reputation as a formidable competitor with a relentless work ethic. His aggressive baseline game, coupled with his exceptional touch and feel at the net, cemented his status as one of the all-time greats of Czech tennis. Kodeš' success on the world stage paved the way for future generations of Czech players to make their mark on the sport.

6

88 VOTES

With her exceptional movement and deceptive shot-making, Lucie Šafářová has consistently dazzled tennis fans and opponents alike throughout her career. As a consummate professional who always brings a spirited and competitive edge to her matches, Šafářová embodies the dedication and passion synonymous with Czech tennis. Equally skilled in both singles and doubles, her relentless drive and determination have made her a perennial threat on the WTA Tour.

Birthplace : Brno, Jihovýchod, Czech Republic

Nationality : Czech Republic
